Script support

The bond command can be used to make an angular bond with a specified bond strength between three specified atoms that are bonded together through two radial bonds. To remove an existing angular bond, use the select command to select it first and then call the remove command. For example, these scripts remove two angular bonds: select abond 4, 5; remove; . The index of an angular bond can be found from its properties window.

